## PART 4 — COMPATIBILITY ROW PICKERS (for Compatibility settings panel)

These replace the `→` navigation rows in the Compatibility panel with
live data from ComponentRepository.

### Compatibility Layer picker (bottom sheet)

```kotlin
@Composable
fun CompatibilityLayerPicker(
    currentVersion: String,
    releases: List<ComponentRelease>,
    onSelect: (ComponentRelease) -> Unit,
    onDownload: (ComponentRelease) -> Unit
) {
    var showSheet by remember { mutableStateOf(false) }

    // Settings row — matches GameHub's row style
    SettingsNavigationRow(
        title        = "Compatibility Layer",
        subtitle     = "Wine / Proton runtime used to run the game",
        currentValue = currentVersion,
        onClick      = { showSheet = true }
    )

    if (showSheet) {
        ModalBottomSheet(
            onDismissRequest = { showSheet = false },
            containerColor = gnBgSurface
        ) {
            Column(modifier = Modifier.padding(bottom = 32.dp)) {
                Text(
                    "Compatibility Layer",
                    style = PluviaTypography.titleMedium.copy(fontWeight = FontWeight.Bold),
                    color = gnTextPrimary,
                    modifier = Modifier.padding(horizontal = 20.dp, vertical = 16.dp)
                )
                Divider(color = gnDivider)

                releases.forEach { release ->
                    Row(
                        modifier = Modifier
                            .fillMaxWidth()
                            .clickable(enabled = release.isInstalled) {
                                onSelect(release)
                                showSheet = false
                            }
                            .padding(horizontal = 20.dp, vertical = 14.dp),
                        horizontalArrangement = Arrangement.SpaceBetween,
                        verticalAlignment = Alignment.CenterVertically
                    ) {
                        Column(modifier = Modifier.weight(1f)) {
                            Row(
                                horizontalArrangement = Arrangement.spacedBy(8.dp),
                                verticalAlignment = Alignment.CenterVertically
                            ) {
                                Text(
                                    release.version,
                                    style = PluviaTypography.bodyMedium.copy(fontWeight = FontWeight.Medium),
                                    color = if (release.isInstalled) gnTextPrimary else gnTextTertiary
                                )
                                if (release.isRecommended) ComponentBadge("RECOMMENDED", gnNeonTeal)
                                if (release.version == currentVersion) ComponentBadge("CURRENT", gnAccentPrimary)
                            }
                            if (!release.isInstalled) {
                                Text(
                                    "%.1f MB — tap to download".format(release.sizeMb),
                                    style = PluviaTypography.bodySmall,
                                    color = gnTextTertiary
                                )
                            }
                        }

                        if (release.version == currentVersion) {
                            Icon(Icons.Default.Check, null, tint = gnNeonTeal, modifier = Modifier.size(20.dp))
                        } else if (!release.isInstalled) {
                            Icon(Icons.Default.Download, null, tint = gnAccentPrimary, modifier = Modifier.size(20.dp))
                        }
                    }
                    Divider(color = gnDivider, modifier = Modifier.padding(horizontal = 20.dp))
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
```

Use the same `CompatibilityLayerPicker` pattern for:
- **GPU Driver** (Turnip versions, filtered by `ComponentType.TURNIP`)
- **DXVK Version** (filtered by `ComponentType.DXVK` and `ComponentType.DXVK_ASYNC`)
- **VKD3D Version** (filtered by `ComponentType.VKD3D`)
- **CPU Translator** (filtered by `ComponentType.BOX64`)
- **Audio Driver** (static list: `PulseAudio`, `PipeWire` — no download needed,
  only affects `WINEDLLOVERRIDES` and `PULSE_LATENCY_MSEC`)

