## DESIGN AND IMPLEMENTATION CONSTRAINTS

- Component rows: same height and chevron style as GameHub screenshot
- Version strings shown right-aligned in gnTextSecondary (e.g. "dxvk-1.10.3-async")
- Download progress: circular indicator inside the action area, not a separate row
- RECOMMENDED badge: gnNeonTeal, ACTIVE badge: gnAccentPrimary, CURRENT badge: gnAccentPrimary
- ACTIVE badge shows the per-game active version (for the current appId), not a global active; two games can use different Proton/DXVK/etc. versions at once
- Stagger GitHub API requests by 100ms each to avoid hitting rate limit
- Cache all releases in Room — show cached data immediately, refresh in background
- If GitHub returns 403 (rate limited), show "Rate limited — cached data shown" toast
- Never block the UI waiting for network — always show cached data first
- On first install with no cached data, show shimmer placeholders
- CPU Core Limit and VRAM Limit sliders in Translation Params → these map to
  DXVK config keys: `dxvk.numAsyncThreads` and `dxvk.deviceLocalMemoryMiB`
- All downloads go to context.cacheDir first, then extracted to context.filesDir
- Never download to external storage — use internal app storage only
- After any Turnip or Mesa component install succeeds, call HardwareProfileCache.invalidate(context)
- All network calls on Dispatchers.IO
- All UI state updates collected on Dispatchers.Main via StateFlow
- No new colors — only existing gn_* tokens from Color.kt
- Fonts: GameNativeFontFamily (Outfit) via PluviaTypography everywhere
